title: Maldives ban: Go to Indian beaches, Israel tells citizens

description: The National Company Law Tribunal has ordered the initiation of insolvency proceedings against Jaiprakash Associates Ltd (JAL). This action comes six years after lenders, led by ICICI Bank, first sought such measures. The decision is expected to impact JAL’s real estate operations in Noida and Greater Noida. However, these operations are on a smaller scale compared to Jaypee Infratech, which was admitted for insolvency in 2018 after ICICI Bank had also moved against JAL.
title: Insolvency proceedings ordered against JAL, flagship firm of Jaiprakash Group

description: The water crisis in the national capital is set to see some progress right after the country elects its new government. On Monday, the Supreme Court directed the Upper Yamuna River Board (UYRB), which includes all the stakeholder states, to convene on June 5 to discuss Delhi's urgent request for additional water supply.
title: SC asks neighbouring states to meet to resolve Delhi water crisis

description: Sensing a recurring trend of unverified allegations and doubts being cast on established electoral processes, such as voter lists, EVMs, VVPATs, or counting during general elections, Chief Election Commissioner Rajiv Kumar expressed concern on Monday. “These were part of the 'mischievous narratives' directed at EC that the poll panel had failed to foresee and prepare against,” he stated.
title: Pattern in fake narratives, we failed to stop them: CEC
3 given life term in Nirbhaya-like 2021 gang-rape case in Bareilly

description: Seven retired judges, six from Madras High Court and one from Patna High Court, have expressed their concerns over the conduct of the upcoming 2024 general elections. In a letter addressed to President Droupadi Murmu and Chief Election Commissioner Rajiv Kumar, they urged protection of "electoral democracy in India." The letter highlights issues in the electoral process.
title: 7 retired HC judges highlight poll issues in letter to Prez, CEC
BJP brass in a huddle, moves on government formation

description: The BJP on Monday asserted that Congress and its allies have lost the trust of the populace and failed to act as a responsible opposition. They have repeatedly undermined democratic institutions by making unfounded accusations against them. Party spokesperson Sudhanshu Trivedi stated at a press conference that the opposition parties have been influenced by "external forces" intent on weakening the spirit of the country's democracy.
title: Congress missed chance to behave as responsible Opposition: BJP

description: On Monday, the Himachal assembly speaker accepted the resignation of three independent MLAs. This event took place a day before the results were to be announced for the state's four Lok Sabha seats and six assembly bypolls. These three MLAs, along with six Congress MLAs, had previously voted for a BJP candidate in the Rajya Sabha polls. Speaker K S Pathania had already disqualified the six rebels, declaring their seats vacant, which reduced the House strength from 68 to 62.
title: Bypolls in Himachal as speaker accepts resignation of 3 independent MLAs

description: A day after Delhi chief minister Arvind Kejriwal asserted that all exit polls that predicted a third term for BJP-led NDA were “fake”, AAP Rajya Sabha MP Sanjay Singh on Monday demanded a ban on exit polls. He further claimed that while there are five seats in Uttarakhand, exit polls are giving BJP six seats, and in Rajasthan where there are 25 seats the results are being shown for 33 seats.
title: AAP’s Sanjay Singh calls for ban on exit polls
8 more Odisha, Rajasthan deaths push heatstroke toll to 219

description: An exit poll conducted by Times Now-ETG on Monday indicates a near-repeat of the 2019 landslide victory for Naveen Patnaik's BJD in the Odisha assembly elections. This projection stands in contrast to other polls that suggest a closer contest with the BJP. The exit poll predicts that BJD could secure between 100 to 115 seats in the 147-member assembly.
title: Naveen set for huge win with 100-115 of 147 seats: An exit poll
111mm rain in 24 hours: Bengaluru breaks 133-year June record

description: As the vote counting approached, Congress continued to raise concerns about the possibility of the results being manipulated. However, it stated that no detailed protest plan had been finalized in case the results mirrored the exit polls. Meanwhile, Congress president Mallikarjun Kharge urged bureaucrats to perform their duties "without coercion or political pressure." This call highlighted the opposition's apprehensions following the exit poll predictions.
title: Congress hopes to prove exit polls wrong, talks of rigging fears
Man gets triple-death sentence for rape, murder of 5-yr-old in Nagpur

description: The Election Commission on Monday turned down the INDIA bloc's request to return to the old system of counting postal ballots before the final round of EVM counting. The EC clarified that changing the counting rules midway was not feasible. The Chief Election Commissioner explained that in most constituencies, the number of postal ballots was relatively low.
title: EC rejects oppn demand, says postal ballots will be counted simultaneously
Police arrest Maoist ‘urban link’ in Raipur

description: The Supreme Court on Monday described the Andhra Pradesh High Court's order providing interim protection from arrest to Macherla MLA Pinnelli Ramakrishna Reddy as a "joke" and "sheer mockery of the justice system." Reddy is accused of damaging a VVPAT device at a polling station. The Supreme Court has also directed Reddy to avoid the counting center in his constituency on Tuesday.
title: ‘Sheer mockery of courts’: SC slams HC shield for rowdy MLA

description: Just hours after the Election Commission turned down Congress general secretary Jairam Ramesh’s request for an additional week to provide factual details of his accusation involving home minister Amit Shah, he submitted his response on Monday evening. However, Ramesh did not disclose any information about the officers involved in his allegations. He stated that they could not be "thrown under the bus."
title: Confronted by EC, Congress’s Jairam Ramesh says can’t name names
Thief breaks into house in Lucknow, dozes off with AC on
Porsche teen’s mom was aware of sample swap plan: Pune cops
Ex-BrahMos engineer gets 14 years’ jail for leaking data to Pakistan

description: Head coach Rahul Dravid remained tight-lipped when questioned about India's opening combination for their T20 World Cup opener against Ireland on June 5. While Rohit Sharma is anticipated to partner with Virat Kohli at the top of the order, there is also speculation regarding Yashasvi Jaiswal as a potential option.
title: 'Not going to reveal our cards, but...': Dravid on opening pair

description: The Serb, who is in pursuit of a record-extending 25th Grand Slam title, notched his 370th match victory at the majors, surpassing Swiss great Roger Federer. However, Djokovic's inconsistent performance in this match may give hope to his title rivals. Djokovic encountered a knee issue during the match but managed to recover and secure the milestone victory.
title: Djokovic shrugs off injury, pips Cerundolo in another French Open epic

description: Sri Lanka's batting performance was abysmal, as they were bowled out for a meager 77 runs, their lowest total in T20 cricket history. South Africa, despite the low target, had to work hard for their victory, eventually reaching the target with six wickets in hand and 3.4 overs to spare.
title: Tough wicket from a batting perspective: Markram

description: Anrich Nortje dismantled Sri Lanka with career-best figures of 4/7, leading South Africa to a six-wicket victory in their T20 World Cup opener on Monday by capitalizing on the available bounce. Playing at a venue where India is set to compete in three of their four Group A league matches, Sri Lanka's decision to bat first proved costly. Nortje, Kagiso Rabada (2/21), and Keshav Maharaj (2/22) combined to claim eight wickets, restricting Sri Lanka to their lowest T20 total of 77 in 19.1 overs.
title: T20 WC: Nortje shines as SA cruise to commanding win over SL

description: Bollywood star Varun Dhawan and wife Natasha Dalal welcome their first child, baby girl, adding a new chapter to their love story.
title: Varun Dhawan and Natasha Dalal blessed with a baby girl

description: The Board of Control for Cricket in India had advertised for the position, and Rahul Dravid's India teammate Gautam Gambhir is considered to be the frontrunner to replace him. "Every tournament is important. Every game that I've coached for India has been very important for me. So for me this is no different just because it is going to be the last one that I'm in charge of," said Dravid.
title: Dravid confirms he won't re-apply for India coach job

description: On Congress rejecting the exit poll results which predict a comfortable majority for the BJP-led NDA, "The Congress party has many people who are very good with language and speak very eloquently and I think these elections will point them towards a new occupation," the minister told news agency ANI. Suggesting new professions for Congress leaders after Lok Sabha results, Chandrasekhar said, "Rahul Gandhi should start a gym. Shashi Tharoor should start an English training institute."
title: 'Rahul should start gym ...': Union min's suggestion for Cong leaders

description: In a press conference, senior AAP leader and Delhi minister Atishi claimed that Kejriwal's weight was measured with three weighing machines during his medical examination in Tihar on Sunday. She also claimed that at a time when temperature in Delhi is ranging from 48 degrees to 50 degrees, Kejriwal was kept in a cell where not even a cooler was provided. "Coolers are provided to even notorious criminals lodged in Tihar. While the popular Chief Minister Kejriwal has not been given the cooler. I want to ask the BJP and the LG how low will they stoop," she said.
title: No cooler for Kejriwal in jail, claims AAP; Tihar official replies

description: Virat Kohli and Yashasvi Jaiswal both sat out India's T20 World Cup warm-up match against Bangladesh. These two players are contenders for partnering skipper Rohit Sharma as the opening batsman. However, former India batsman and Star Sports commentator Navjot Singh Sidhu has confidently identified the pair that will open for India against Ireland on June 5.
title: T20 WC: Predicting India's playing XI in 'Sherry pa' style
On eve of counting day, Kharge makes appeal to bureaucrats

description: The Enforcement Directorate (ED), in a supplementary chargesheet against K Kavitha, Bharat Rashtra Samithi (BRS) leader and daughter of Telangana chief minister K Chandrashekar Rao, has alleged that she paid a kickback of ₹100 crore to the leaders of Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) in connection with the Delhi excise policy case. The agency also said that more than Rs 1,100 crore was laundered in the alleged Delhi excise scam.
title: Kavitha paid ₹100 cr kickback to AAP leaders, deleted data from 9 phones: ED chargesheet

description: Team India  wicketkeeper-batter Sanju Samson admitted that amidst the intense pressure of the IPL, he couldn't help but ponder about his chances of being selected  in for the upcoming T20 World Cup. Samson appeared quietly confident in his abilities, acknowledging that the tournament could put his skills to the test.
title: '10 years of lots and lots of failures...': Samson

description: The judges expressed concern over the ECI’s refusal to disclose the exact numbers of votes cast in each booth of every constituency.
title: Former judges express concern over the way Lok Sabha election was conducted

description: Pakistan are set to launch their ICC T20 World Cup 2024 campaign against the co-hosts United States, on June 6 at the Grand Prairie Stadium in Dallas. Led by Babar Azam, the squad is diligently honing their skills in practice sessions to prepare for their tournament opener. The Green Shirts have been observed in intense yet enjoyable practice sessions. Captain Babar Azam, known for using nicknames to maintain a light-hearted atmosphere, playfully came up with a nickname for Azam Khan, the son of the legendary Moin Khan.
title: Did Babar Azam body-shame Azam Khan?

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi, who led a high-charge election campaign, is likely to get a historic third term, equalling the record of the country's first prime minister Jawahar Lal Nehru. But this is not the only record the BJP hopes to achieve. As results start to come in from 8am on June 4, all eyes will be on the final seat tally of the NDA to see if it actually manages to get '400 paar' (over 400 seats). The only time any party achieved this target was in the 1984 General Elections when the Rajiv Gandhi-led Congress won 414 seats (of the 541 that voted).
title: Throwback to 1984 elections: When Congress got '400 paar'

description: The International Cricket Council (ICC) on Monday announced a groundbreaking prize money of $11.25 million for the Men’s T20 World Cup 2024, setting a new record for the tournament. The winners of the ICC Men's T20 World Cup 2024 is set to receive at least $2.45 million - the highest prize amount in the history of the event.
title: ICC announces record prize money for T20 World Cup

description: Islamabad High Court clears former Prime Minister Imran Khan and ex-foreign minister Shah Mahmood Qureshi of leaking state secrets. Khan and Qureshi will still remain in jail for another conviction related to a classified cable leak in 2022 and May 9 case respectively. The cipher case revolves around a diplomatic document that, according to the FIA charge sheet, was allegedly not returned by Khan.
title: Pakistan court acquits ex-PM Imran Khan in cypher case

description: In preparation for the upcoming event, Nassau's police department has collaborated with various organizations, including the Federal Bureau of Investigation, the US Department of Homeland Security, and the New York Police Department, among others. This coordinated effort aims to ensure the safety and security of all participants and attendees throughout the duration of the competition.
title: Snipers deployed in New York stadium ahead of SL-SA match
EC rejects Jairam's plea for more time to back claims against Shah

description: The Lok Sabha elections, overseen by the Election Commission of India (ECI), will announce results on June 4. Stay updated on the ECI website and Voter Helpline App.
title: Lok Sabha election results: Where and how to watch live vote counting
LS poll results: When, where and how to track counting of votes

description: India cricketer Kedar Jadhav announced his retirement from all forms of cricket on Monday. The announcement, which closely mirrored the retirement note of former Indian captain MS Dhoni, emphasized the strong bond between the two cricketers. Jadhav shared a slideshow of photos from his career on Instagram, accompanied by a Kishore Kumar song.
title: Kedar Jadhav announces retirement from all forms of cricket
Israel promotes Lakshadweep after Maldives bars Israeli citizens

description: Former engineer Nishant Agarwal from BrahMos Aerospace Pvt Ltd was sentenced to life imprisonment by the Nagpur district court for leaking sensitive technical information to Pakistan's ISI, leading to his arrest in 2018. He also received a 14-year rigorous imprisonment and a Rs 3,000 fine. BrahMos Aerospace is a collaborative venture between DRDO and NPO Mashinostroyenia.
title: Ex-BrahMos Aerospace engg gets life term for spying for Pak's ISI

description: State Bank of India's market capitalization surpassed Rs 8 lakh crore as the stock hit a 52-week high on exit polls predictions.
title: SBI market cap crosses Rs 8 lakh crore; stock hits 52-week high
'Not right to doubt everyone': CEC slams Jairam Ramesh

description: Munawar Faruqui's private life was revealed during his time on Bigg Boss 17. He recently married makeup artist Mehzabeen Coatwala, with the couple now sharing their romance on social media.
title: Munawar's wife proud of him; drops pictures from his recent gig

description: A viral video shows a dramatic incident in Jammu & Kashmir involving a Tata Punch SUV in a rollover accident. The driver miraculously escaped as the SUV tumbled down a steep slope, emphasizing safe driving practices in challenging terrains.
title: Watch: Tata Punch tumbles down mountain, driver survives

description: Stock market ideas: Even the most conservative estimate predicts a minimum of 316 seats for the alliance. Although the NDA may not achieve its ambitious 'Abki Baar 400 Paar' goal, traders anticipate the Nifty to surpass the 24,000 mark this week.
title: What are brokerages betting on based on Modi’s expected win?
On eve of LS poll results, Congress wary of moves to topple govt

description: JDU leader Anil Kumar was brutally murdered in Maua village, Nalanda district, Bihar. He served as a polling agent during the Lok Sabha elections and faced threats from the RJD. The attackers ambushed him on his way to the farm, leading to his tragic death.
title: JD(U) leader hacked to death in Bihar's Nalanda

description: Matthew Hayden, an Australian cricketer, has emphasized the importance of a left-right combination in India's batting order ahead of their upcoming T20 World Cup opener against Ireland. He believes Virat Kohli should open the innings, while Rohit Sharma would be more effective at number four to control the middle order. However, there is speculation that India might opt for Rohit and Yashasvi Jaiswal.
title: 'Virat Kohli has to open or he does not play...': Hayden
'Never went missing': CEC on 'Laapata Gentlemen' memes

description: Google CEO Sundar Pichai is thrilled about the 2024 ICC T20 Men’s Cricket World Cup. In a post on X, he expressed excitement for his favorite sport growing globally and wished luck to all participating teams.
title: Pichai has this ‘special message’ on T20 World Cup coming to the US

description: World Bicycle Day, established by the United Nations in 2018, promotes cycling for transportation, health, and sustainability, advocating for improved infrastructure and safer roads.
title: World Bicycle Day: How few hrs of cycling weekly has health benefits
'Cartels gone', Haryana auctions 60% liquor vending zones

description: India's manufacturing sector experienced a slowdown in growth during May, with the HSBC final India Manufacturing Purchasing Managers' Index falling to 57.5 from 58.8 in April.
title: India's manufacturing growth slows to 3-mnth low, but...

description: Former cricketer Aakash Chopra has raised concerns about Rohit Sharma led Indian team's readiness for the T20 World Cup, despite being among the favorites. He questioned why the team is still finalizing its playing XI and argued that players should have been informed of their roles well before the tournament began.
title: 'Are India underprepared for yet another T20 World Cup?'

description: The exit poll has predicted a clean sweep by the United Democratic Front (UDF), which has an alliance with the Congress, in the Lok Sabha election in Kerala. It has predicted 16 seats for UDF and two seats for the LDF while it’s neck and neck race in two seats.
title: Exit poll predicts massive slump in Rahul's vote share in Wayanad

description: May 2024 tech layoffs included 9,742 job cuts across 39 companies, with Toshiba announcing 4,000 job cuts and planning to move office functions to Kawasaki.
title: Tech layoffs 2024 touch 89,000: Google, Microsoft, TikTok, Tesla and these companies cut hundreds of jobs in May

description: Former Indian Test opener Wasim Jaffer responds to allegations about T20 World Cup schedule favoring Team India. On Sunday, an English cricket website alleged that the T20 World Cup schedule favours Team India specially the timing of the semi-finals of the tournament. In this year's T20 World Cup India face Ireland (June 5), Pakistan (June 9), the United States (June 12) and Canada (June 15) in the group phase of the tournament.
title: Jaffer's savage reply to post alleging advantage to Team India

description: The Indian Air Force airdropped a Mahindra Thar SUV in Rudraprayag near the Kedarnath Temple base camp using a Chinook helicopter. As per reports, authorities intend to deploy two similar SUVs to assist pilgrims encountering difficulties during the trek.
title: Mahindra Thar ‘flies’ to Kedarnath for pilgrimage service: Video viral
Ahead of Lok Sabha election results, Nitish Kumar meets PM Modi

description: Despite the nepotism debate, experts say that despite the internal push, it all boils down to a mix of talent, luck and the right offers. Ramesh Taurani, film producer says, "At the end of the day, success is a mix of talent and luck, and that goes for everyone, whether or not he/she is a star kid. The only edge a star kid has is that they can meet the producer directly, even more than once, but beyond that, nothing is guaranteed."
title: Why couldn't these star kids make it big in acting?
Akasa flight diverted to Ahmedabad after receiving 'security alert'

description: Former Indian captain MS Dhoni is praised for his balance between technology and instinct. Former Indian cricketer Mohammad Kaif commends Dhoni and Rohit Sharma for blending tech with common sense. Kaif highlights Dhoni's unique game-reading ability, emphasizing that under match pressure, instincts and mental strength are crucial, areas where Dhoni excels.
title: 'Like MS Dhoni, captain Rohit Sharma has achieved a balance': Kaif

description: The 2024 T20 World Cup has started with the USA and West Indies securing victories on the opening day, followed by Namibia's Super Over win against Oman. India's first glimpse of the team was during their warm-up match against Bangladesh, where they dominated with a comfortable 60-run victory. Yashasvi Jaiswal's absence from the match has sparked speculation about whether he will be dropped.
title: Finch on why India should persist with Yashasvi-Rohit as openers

description: Bigg Boss 13's Dalljiet Kaur and her estranged husband, Kenya-based businessman Nikhil Patel, are in a legal battle. Nikhil issued Dalljiet a legal notice citing violations of Indian laws regarding social media posts accusing him of an extramarital affair.
title: Nikhil Patel issues estranged wife Dalljiet Kaur written cease letter

description: Congress chief Sonia Gandhi stated on Monday that the party is "hopeful" that the election results will be "completely opposite" to what the exit polls have projected, one day before the 2024 Lok Sabha results are expected to be announced. P​ollsters on Saturday predicted third term for the BJP-led NDA with majority of them predicting 350-400 seats for NDA.
title: 'Wait & watch': What Sonia Gandhi said on LS exit poll results

description: The exit polls projections suggest a landslide victory for the NDA, reaffirming the BJP's strong electoral performance and the leadership of Prime Minister Narendra Modi. If the predictions hold true, it would mark a historic mandate for the ruling coalition, surpassing its previous performance in the 2014 general elections.
title: As exit polls predict Modi 3.0, BJP cadres plan mega roadshow

description: Indian equity benchmarks BSE Sensex and Nifty 50 reached record highs driven by exit polls predicting a strong mandate for PM Modi's third term.
title: Stock market rally adds Rs 12 lakh crore to investors’ wealth

description: Intense thundershowers and heavy rain hit Bengaluru following the Southwest Monsoon setting over Karnataka Coast. The city experienced a record spell of rain, breaking a 133-year-old meteorological record for the wettest day in June.
title: Bengaluru rain breaks 133-year-old record for the wettest day in June

description: Namibia clinched a thrilling Super Over win against Oman to kick off their T20 World Cup campaign at the Kensington Oval. Ruben Trumpelmann's historic feat of two wickets in two balls set the stage for Namibia's disciplined bowling display. Jan Frylinck's steady 45 and a resilient Super Over sealed the victory for Namibia.
title: T20 WC: Namibia beat Oman in first Super Over in 12 years

description: Adani Group's stocks surged as predictions of Modi's victory in the Lok Sabha elections triggered a market rally. Adani Power, Adani Ports, and Adani Enterprises led the gains.
title: Adani group stocks surf on Modi wave! Rs 1.4 lakh crore m-cap added

description: Pakistan cricketers face criticism at home ahead of T20 World Cup. Ahmed Shehzad challenges skipper Babar Azam to win 2024 edition. Former PCB chairman Ramiz Raja criticized team after T20I series loss to England. Led by Babar Azam and coached by Gary Kirtsen, Pakistan are scheduled to open their campaign against USA on Thursday and will clash with India on Sunday.
title: 'World Cup jeetwa ke dain...': Ahmed Shehzad challenges Babar Azam

description: India captain Rohit Sharma has not yet decided the team's playing XI for the 2024 ICC T20 World Cup, despite their win against Bangladesh. Yashasvi Jaiswal is likely not to feature in the campaign opener against Ireland, and Virat Kohli will open the batting with Sharma. Former India cricketer Irfan Pathan has consistently opposed Kohli opening with Rohit in the World Cup.
title: Virat or Yashasvi - who will open with Rohit? Playing XI debate heats up

description: A Noida businessman lost Rs 9 crore to a trading scam that started on a WhatsApp group. The victim lodged a complaint with the city’s Cyber Crime police station, and Rs 1.62 crore in his bank account was frozen.
title: Bizman loses Rs 9cr to WhatsApp trading scam: Tips to stay safe

description: Munna, also known as  Mohammad Alikhan and Manojkumar Bhawarlal Gupta, a notorious criminal and habitual absconder, had played a crucial role in the 1993 Mumbai blasts by escorting Tiger Memon, the prime accused, from Mumbai to Raigad for the Shekhadi landing of a large cache of arms, ammunition, hand grenades, and RDX. He also assisted in transporting the cache back to Mumbai.
title: 1993 Mumbai blast convict killed in jail was Tiger Memon associate

description: Donald Trump addressed the 'lock her up' chants directed at Hillary Clinton during his rallies, emphasizing unity and national progress post-election.
title: Trump denies saying 'lock her up' about 2016 rival Clinton

description: India's cricket fans are eagerly awaiting the 2024 ICC T20 World Cup in the USA, having started their preparations with a victory over Bangladesh in warm-up match in New York. The team will face Ireland on Wednesday and Pakistan in a group stage clash on June 9. Former cricketers emphasize the importance of supporting experienced players.
title: 'Ab waqt aa gaya hai': Experts on India's chances to end trophy drought
BSF constable assaulted by miscreants at India-Bangladesh border

description: A viral video showed Bollywood actor Raveena Tandon being pushed outside her Bandra home. Khar police, led by Zonal DCP Raj Tilak Roushan, sent both parties for medical examination at a public hospital. Allegations of assault by her driver were refuted by police, who conducted an investigation and obtained witness statements. No official statement from Raveena Tandon has been released.
title: In viral clip, group shoves Raveena Tandon during spat with driver

description: The Norway Chess tournament saw Magnus Carlsen solidify his lead with a victory over Ding Liren, reaching 12 points. Fabiano Caruana's win over Hikaru Nakamura left Nakamura one point behind Carlsen. Indian players faced setbacks; R Praggnanandhaa lost in the Armageddon tiebreaker to Firouzja Alireza, and R Vaishali was defeated by Wenjun Ju, leaving her just half a point behind the leaders.
title: Brother-sister Indian duo of Pragg and Vaishali suffer defeats

description: Former cricketers Sanjay Manjrekar and Sanjay Bangar have defended Hardik Pandya's selection for the T20 World Cup, citing his exceptional performances in past international tournaments. Manjrekar believes the selectors made the right choice in selecting Pandya, citing his impressive World Cup record. Pandya played the all-rounder's role well in the 2019 World Cup.
title: 'Big-match player': Ex-cricketers back Hardik Pandya to shine

description: 61 people in north India have died from a heatwave, including 23 poll workers from the Lok Sabha election. WHO warns against antimicrobial resistance. Hyperbaric oxygen therapy delivers high oxygen levels under pressure. Read today health news briefing here. Your morning dose of health updates, news and latest guidelines are all here:
title: Heatwave kills over 60, WHO warns against microbial resistance

description: 141 suspected heatstroke deaths, 26 confirmed after post-mortem. PM Modi reviews situation in Odisha. Deaths in western parts, Sundargarh, Balangir districts. Sambalpur reports 18 suspected cases.
title: Odisha heat toll rises to 141 with 45 more suspected deaths

description: After a successful stint with Gujarat Titans in the IPL where he acted as mentor and batting coach, Gary Kirsten will be plying his trade with Pakistan as the country's white-ball coach. India take on Pakistan on June 9 in the T20 World Cup in New York's Nassau County Ground and Kirsten, who will be in the green dug out, could be carrying some trade secrets about the Indian players which the Pakistan team can exploit.
title: T20 World Cup: Will Pakistan benefit from the Gary Kirsten impact?
